Place a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} on top rack (for 4 servings, use 2 lightly oiled baking sheets{} on top and middle racks) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

> Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. Season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken or sausage; cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, about 4-6 minutes. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2.5%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and cook, stirring, until lightly browned and softened, about ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Use pan used for chicken or sausage here.

While zucchini cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomatoes, garlic, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

In a second small bowl, combine @ricotta cheese{4%oz}, half the lemon zest, ½ tsp olive oil (1 tsp for 4 servings), and lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Carefully place @flatbreads{2} on prepared baking sheet (divide between both prepared sheets for 4 servings). Evenly spread flatbreads with lemon ricotta. Top with zucchini and tomatoes, cut sides up.

Bake on top rack (top and middle racks for 4) until flatbreads are golden brown, about ~{10-12%minutes}.

> Top flatbreads with chicken or sausage along with veggies.

Meanwhile, pick @parsley{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Once flatbreads are done, garnish with parsley, remaining lemon zest, and @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste. Drizzle with @honey{2%tsp}, then slice into pieces.

Divide between plates and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.